text: Menginap di sini 3 hari 2 malam, pesan 2 kamar lewat online web The Wujil 1 bulan sebelumnya. So far ok, semoga bisa kembali lagi di lain kesempatan. Terima kasih The Wujil utk pengalaman menginap yg menyenangkan.

text:
Liburan akhir tahun 2017 kami sekeluarga memutuskan untuk stay di Semarang selama beberapa hari.. Dan hari pertama kami menginap di Wujil resort.. Suami sangat tertarik dg ulasan mengenai Wujil dan ingin membuktikannya sendiri.. Benar kami check-in pada tanggal 20 des 2017.. Proses check-in cukup cepat.. Begitu masuk kamar saya merasa cukup puas dg kondisi kamar yg cukup luas, TV LCD yg besar dan chanel TV yg banyak pilihan,  ada kulkas kecil, ada water heater untuk membuat teh dan kopi.. Kebersihan kamar cukup terjaga begitu juga dg kamar mandi yg saya rasa pas ukuranya pas ga kesempitan.. Si kecil juga nyaman berada di dalam kamar.. Kebetulan kamar kami berada dilantai yg ada fasilitas playground indoornya.. Wow si kecil yg baru berusia 2 th excited bgt main disitu.. Over all hotel ini mengesankan bagi saya. 
1. Staffnya ramah dan sangat membantu
2. Cocok untuk tempat menginap bersama keluarga
3. Pemandangan sepanjang joging track sangat Indah di tambah udara pagi hari Ungaran yg sangat segar membatu merefresh kepenatan otak
4. Banyak spot foto kece di sini buat para pecinta selfie pasti akan suka dg suasana dan keindahan wujil resort 
5. Wifi kenceng 
6. Sarapan pagi bervariasi dan cukup pas dilidah ditambah ada staff yg menanyakan review tentang rasa dan variant sarapan
7. Playground outdoor nya juga sangat nyaman untuk bermain anak" sikecil senang sekali berada diarea playground 
Bahkan Ibu Mertua saya juga merasa cocok menginap di Wujil
Semoga review saya bisa membantu para traveller untuk memilih hotel yg pas.. Untuk Wujil semoga bisa memperbaiki apa yg kurang dan memingkatkan apa yang sudah baik..

text:
Initially we were supposed to spend our time at Karimun Island but due to bad weather, we directed our trip back to Semarang and decided to go to Ungaran and stumble upon this hotel online and decided to gave it a go and we made a right decision. 

The hotel is new, the room is spacious (the entire hotel is spacious) we love the Wifi! super fast and the staff are friendly and helpful. One thing that impresses us the most is when we decided to leave the hotel at 3 AM to catch the sunrise at Borobudur, Magelang and we spoke to the receptionist about early breakfast and impressively for a hotel within that budget is able to provide us with breakfast box! we were just trying our luck in asking and my jaw drops when they said they will prepare it for us and ready at front desk at 3 AM...very well done! your team at the hotel is amazing and also a compliment to your friendly security team. 

On another note, nothing is perfect, the restaurant on the other hand needs improvement, on my first day of stay, I decided to ordered coffee at the restaurant and the waiter asked me if I want a sachet or machine coffee so I said machine and he unawarely told me "the price is different, it's more expensive" which I found quite rude, he should just point out a section in the menu with the machine coffee pricing (if you dont have one yet, make one) and when the coffee arrived, it was already sweetened so much (I assume around 20% of the glass is sugar) and I told him that why there are sugar in my coffee and it's too much and his reply is "it's our standard here" so I gave him some input and he didn't seems so pleased and when my food arrived, there were no cutleries or even napkins. the last day when we had breakfast, my friend ordered a coffee and again, it was served with so much sugar, I guess they didn't take my input into consideration. one more flaw, the swimming pool is open for public which makes it noisy and full of screaming children and their moms and the water level in the pool is not full. 

However, it's still an excellent hotel to stay! Thank you for the experience
title: Budget stay with excellent facility and service

text:
Wowwwww...!!! It was my expression.

This resort is just AWESOME...!!! The big area of the location, the design, the service.., everything is just right on the money...!!

We were travelling by car from Jakarta. When we reach this resort, all of our tiredness was paid off by staying at this resort.

Not just this is a new hotel, but the design is just so nice, especially the convention building.

We booked 2 (two) standard rooms, the rooms were clean, the bathroom was clean. So nice... I hope they can maintain it for long time of their existence.

The breakfast was not offering much varieties but it was good enough.

The only concern that I have is they don't separate SMOKING  and NON-SMOKING area. With that huge restaurant area, it will not be difficult to provide non-smoking area.

Apart of the hotel design, I saw that something was not looking right, the tissue boxes they provide in the restaurant is cheap boxes. It would not cost much to find and use more ethnic tissue boxes so that the hotel will have a sync look with the whole design. Yes it was a small and less important thing, but it catches my eyes....hehehe... I regret that I did not remember to mentioned about this thing to hotel staff during check out. I want this hotel to be big and become one of the talk of the people when visiting this area.

One other thing that's quite odd is the location of the swimming pool in the parking area, so people have to walk nearly across the parking area to get to the swimming pool. But it was a nice swimming pool.
I would love to know that one day, they figure out how to make walking to the swimming pool is more enjoyable by designing and building a garden walk or something.....

I love the garden of this hotel, well design and so enjoyable for a morning walk with Mount Ungaran View.

Would I come back to this hotel again ?? 100% YES....!!!
title: Amazing new Resort !!

text:
The reservation and check in&out process was seamless. The staffs are friendly and helpful.

However, the facilities and issues management need further improvement. First, we saw dry lizard feces on the tv table when we arrived. Faucets inside the bathroom were leaked but still usable. Our air conditioner was also leaked when we arrived. They sent maintenance staffs to repair the AC when we were already inside the room -hence we couldn’t get a proper rest while they were working. We decided to take a walk outside as the room was getting dirty due to the AC maintenance. When we got back, the room was already cleaned BUT the AC was still leaked. Although the leakage was better than before, but still disturbing and unsafe since we were traveling with toddlers. We asked to move to another room but they only have one family room -which we booked. They didn’t offer to move to connecting rooms or other options. No gesture was given to compensate this inconvenience, even the simplest ones.

The swimming pool was located in the middle of a construction site. We needed to walk through the construction site to reach the pool -which was quite strange since we had to walk pass some construction workers with our swimsuits (we put on some clothes on top of our swimsuits, of course. But still didn’t feel comfortable walking pass a lot of workers with our damped hair and clothes after swimming)
title: Further improvements needed

text:
1. Bedroom: Clean and spacious. Connecting rooms are provided

2. Bathroom: clean and well-maintained. Liquid Soap/shampoo dispenser is installed. That means you hardly need to worry about running out of soap/shampoo. Water pressure and hot/cold water works well.

3. Breakfast: this is where I have to speak harsh. One server have to maintain multiple food stations and I saw how one server juggling from serving fried rice to cooking a fried egg and then serving a dessert. You can imagine the queue. Long story short, the food stations are greatly understaffed. Food quality? I wonder when they actually had a food quality control. Most of them taste bland.

4. Parking: large parking spots. Not really a secured and roofed car park so expect your vehicle to get drenched by rains

5. Location: perfect for those who want to explore Ungaran (Cimory, Dusun Semilir). Distance-wise quite good because it’s roughly in the middle between Semarang and Solo. The property has a large garden where you can take a great walk in the early morning. 

6. Price: spend 520k Rupiah per night. This could be a great value-for-money if they do justice to breakfast experience.

7. Overall: Good experience overall. Will I stay again? Yes. Will I take a breakfast package again? Nope. The breakfast department really needs some great improvement
title: Good “Green” Stay at the heart of Ungaran

It such a pleasant to stay here with my family last month. I ordered from the website (it had cheaper rate than tr**vel*ka) about a week ago from my travel date, i ordered 3 rooms and requested  connected room for 2 of it and the all in the same floor. And they made it!

The room was clean and comfortable. It had a balcony with 2 chairs and 1 coffee table that faced the pool or garden area. The amenities and toiletries were very complete.
The swimming pool was pretty large. It divided into 2 areas; the kids pool and the regular pool. They even have a kids playground beside the swimming pool and it's pretty big enough for your child to play around. They also have a huge garden, a mini lake, a deck and a convention hall.

Despite all the great facilities, i think they should improve the breakfast serving. Because of the pandemic, the buffet must be served by the restaurant's staff and they only got one man to serve the buffet island (it consisted of: main course, salad, side dish, toast, cereal and drink) so it took a long time to get your meal. I suggest to put 2 men there at least.

text: Wujil has great facilities, but not enough maintenance. There is a park vast enough to do a relaxing morning jog or rented for a party, an outdoor swimming pool, a children's playground, a ballroom in its own building, a gift shop with delicious gelato~~, and a rooftop dining. I enjoyed my stay with my family as we booked 2 rooms. The balconies might be a waste of area, but the room was big enough for each four of us to sleep. One of the rooms had dirty sheets when we checked in, but as soon as we complained they took care of it and changed the whole bed sheets. I love the rooftop since we hanged out to play cards and drink beer there. The room service has low price but the food is great! All the employees are kind and hospitable.
title: A fine hotel

text:
It was a fantastic stay at The Wujil Resorts & Convention. I booked 5 rooms for 9 persons and we were given rooms adjacent to each other. We were there for my Engagement Ceremony and ALL of my guests were very very satisfied with the service, cleanliness and customer service given by the staffs.

From the moment we step into the hotel compound to the time that I check out, every step was served with the most courteous Customer Service ever, by the staffs. Our room had a Balcony facing the Ungaran Mountain. It was a beautiful to wake up and feel the fresh air of Ungaran. Breakfast was delicious with a wide spread of American and Indonesian Breakfast Dishes. There was also Jamu as part of the dishes served! The location of the Breakfast Restaurant was at the 4th storey, a semi-outdoor, rooftop restaurant. Eating breakfast with the sight of the beautiful Ungaran Mountain accompanying us at the side. Everybody in my group was busy insta-storying and instagram-ing their experience. Room service was great too. Food was delivered hot and on time. When there was a slight delay in the food delivery to the room, the staff would courteously call us to inform of it. Perfect! Room cleanliness was awesome. Toilet was clean and the bedsheets were changed every single day. 

The hotel do have airport transfer/pick-up service too and it was so convenient for hotel guests! The driver was very friendly and helpful. On top of that, on one of the night, at 2am, I had to print a document urgently and the reception staff helped me print it for free, at that wee hours of the night. That is what I would call service beyond the call of duty.

I will definitely book this hotel again for my entourage during my Wedding in Semarang in July, 2019. Thank you to all of the staffs, the management team, the restaurant and kitchen crews, the doorman, the security guards and the cleaners for delivering the best customer service to my guests. Well done!
title: Marvellous Hotel with Great Mountain View & Fantastic Customer Service!

text: Stay for a night in Wujil, we had a very pleasant stay. This hotel completely had what we need. Located in Ungaran area, not in the downtown area, so instead of the high building, you will get a beautiful view & scenery that pamper your eyes and soul. This hotel have so many attraction outdoor spots. It's good for family vacation. Your kids will not get bored for so many things can be done. We stayed in the 3rd floor with a great view of mountains near Bandungan area. Each room has its own balcony, and it is quite surprising. Me and my hubby spent some hours at our balcony and it was great moment. We booked two room with connecting door so we can keep our eyes to the kiddos as well.Room quite big with comfy bed. The amenities inside are also great. You can ask pool view room for better view. Unfortunately they don't provide soap near the wash bin area, you need to get it from the shower area.Breakfast was on the 4th floor with again, beautiful view. Some part is outdoor. The food were not quite to various but yah not bad. It will be greater if hotel can provide more options. But the taste was quite good. Overall, we glad for our stays here.
title: Pleasant Stay on Affordable Price

text:
It's a local name hotel under TAUZIA - France hotel chain to my understanding. And this hotel opened for operation around 8 months ago. So, overall the hotel complex relatively new.
Room spacious enough, clean and neat. Equipment (A/C, Cable TV, Wifi, Hot water maker) are working well. Not fridge here. Hot and cold water for shower are good and stable but to wash your hand you need to get the soap from the shower cubicle. They not provide you a soap bar, while other standard aminities provide.
Front Office Staff are helpfull but their English langguage have strong blend of local dialec. Check in / out process smoth and consider fast.
Breakfast menu somehow could be improve (very limited amount and variety of USA / European dishes), while local cuisine having suficient varieties even the taste just average. Cuttlery set not according to the International standard (no knife provide - only spoon and fork).
The dissapointment was a young Salesman Staff, asking for inputs and comments but when I gave the inputs and comments he simply explained it is not the hotel standard so they not provided and to have a cost down??? What an attitude.
It's too bad they didn't get the correct hospitality attitude.
title: Prety good hotel at a suburb area with lack of hospitality attitude
